  "why": "The paper provides a partial diagnostic insight by characterizing the properties of discovered failures for one of the experimental subjects. Specifically, for the Coop Navi (MARL) task, the authors analyze and plot the spatial distribution of agent positions in the crash-triggering scenarios discovered by their method and a baseline. They observe that the baseline method tends to find crashes when agents are positioned near the boundary of the valid input space, whereas their method finds crashes across more varied positions. This analysis characterizes a property of the discovered failures (their location in the state space) and correlates them with the input structure, which aligns with the 'Medium' rating. However, it does not link these failures to underlying model vulnerabilities like training data bias or overfitting, which would be required for a 'High' rating.",
